Reasoning: The paper deals with analyzing emergent processes in cellular automata, which involves concepts from multiple sub-fields of computer science. The use of tools for coarse-graining and identifying which coarse-grainings express an automaton's dynamics well suggests a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The investigation of examples in Conway's Game of Life and Hopfield networks suggests a focus on discrete structures (cs.DS) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The formalization of the notion of emergent processes suggests a focus on systems and control (cs.SY).
